\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish-mexico
Let's use the solution from the previous task with the following changes,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta\rightarrow\gamma$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=0$
\end_inset

, which is the data given here.
 So the state vector for this problem, expressed in the basis 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ |+\rangle,|-\rangle\right\} $
\end_inset

 is written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
|\mathbf{S\cdot\hat{n}};+\rangle=\cos\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)|+\rangle+\sin\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)|-\rangle\text{.}
\]

\end_inset

Now, we know that given an arbitrary ket 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{|\alpha\rangle}}$
\end_inset

, the probability that it will collapse into some base ket 
\begin_inset Formula $|a\rangle$
\end_inset

