\begin_layout Standard

\lang spanish-mexico
In our case, the probability that when measuring 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{x}$
\end_inset

 we get 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\hbar}{2}$
\end_inset

 is the probability that the ket 
\begin_inset Formula $|\mathbf{S\cdot\hat{n}};+\rangle$
\end_inset

 colapse in 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|S_{x};+\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{P}\left(S_{x};+\right)=\left|\left\langle S_{x};+\right.\left|\mathbf{S\cdot\hat{n}};+\right\rangle \right|^{2}\text{.}
\]

\end_inset

On the other hand, we know that the ket 
\begin_inset Formula $|S_{x};+\rangle$
\end_inset

 is given by
