but, if we use the identity 
\begin_inset Formula $2\sin\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)\cos\left(\frac{\gamma}{2}\right)=\sin\left(\gamma\right)$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{P}\left(S_{x};+\right)=\frac{1}{2}\left(1+\sin\left(\gamma\right)\right)\text{.}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

